<item>
            <title>[HIVE-923] Hive should not use CombineHiveInputFormat by default because it breaks for hadoop 0.20 releases.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-923</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-5759&quot; title=&quot;IllegalArgumentException when CombineFileInputFormat is used as job InputFormat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-5759&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-5759&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is committed to Hadoop 0.20 on 19/Oct/09 but not released yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should not use CombineHiveInputFormat for hadoop 0.20 for now. Otherwise all users will encounter problems using Hive trunk against Hadoop 0.20.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can switch the default back when a new release from hadoop 0.20 comes out.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
